========================================
PURPOSE:
========================================
Shortcode methods allow to excecute PHP code fragments from the WYSIWYG editor. This can be handy,
if you want to output some "dynamic stuff" from inside the WYSIWYG editor without modifying the template.
The following shortcode methods are implemented:

SHORTCODE TO PROTECT E-MAIL ADRESSES:
Parts of the visible E-Mail address is obfuscated: @ --> (at), . --> (dot). The mailto link part is protected 
by a simple Javascript encryption and will be decrypted when clicked and openend in your mail program.
 - [HideMailto email='yourmail@domain.com' subject='optional_mail_subject']
 - [HideMailto email='yourmail@domain.com' subject='optional_mail_subject']mail_link_text[HideMailto]

SHORTCODE TO SHOW RANDOM IMAGE WITH COLORBOX EFFECT:
This shortcode displays a random image with colorbox effect from a subfolder inside Silverstripe /assets folder
 - [RandomImage folder="subfolder_in_assets" align="left|right"]

SHORTCODE TO SHOW RANDOM QUOTE FROM A TEXT FILE:
Shortdoce to display a random quote from a CSV (comma separated value) file within a subfolder located inside Silverstripe /assets folder:
 - [RandomQuote csv_file="subfolder_in_assets/quotes.csv"]

A valid CSV file must follow the syntax below (first header line required)
"quote"|"author"
"your first quote goes here"|"author name"
"next quote goes here"|"autor of this quote"

========================================
INSTALLATION:
========================================
This module requires CMS Silverstripe in version v2.4.5 (not tested for upcoming v3).
Ftp the module to the root folder of your Silverstripe installation and rename the folder to "cws-shortcode".
Make the module available to Silverstripe via visiting URL: "yourdomain.com/dev/build?flush=all".

========================================
USAGE OF THE SHORTCODE MODULE:
========================================
The following [shortcode] statements can be added to a WYSIWYG page.
 [HideMailto email='yourmail@domain.com' subject='optional_mail_subject']
 [HideMailto email='yourmail@domain.com' subject='optional_mail_subject']mail_link_text[HideMailto]
 [RandomImage folder="subfolder_in_assets" align="left|right"]
 [RandomQuote csv_file="subfolder_in_assets/quotes.csv"]

========================================
Tip:
========================================
You can style the output to your needs by adapting the template files and/or css files located in /templates and /css folder.
